Dear TI-USA Corporate Supporters:  We are delighted to report that yesterday the OAS General Assembly approved a resolution calling for the creation of a follow-up mechanism for the Inter-American Convention Against Corruption.
As you know, TI has been working toward this goal for over two years.
The agreement provides for a Committee of Experts to select the provisions of the Convention and countries to be reviewed and for the possibility of consultations with civil society.
